ween open circle closed by horizontal bar and closed ovoid form with horizontal bar; phi has a small circular eye; sigma has standard form with horizontal top and bottom storkes; omicron is approximately the same size as other letters.",[202,206],{"type":39,"l":203,"from":41,"to":204,"h":205,"unit":43},"Lines 1-5","line5","30-45",{"type":45,"l":46,"from":41,"to":42,"unit":43},{"_":208,"notBefore":209,"notAfter":210,"precision":16},"2nd century BCE(?)",-200,-101,[212,213],{"_":53,"type":54,"ref":55},{"_":57,"type":58,"ref":59,"offset":60},[215],[63,64],{"_":150,"role":151,"ref":152},{"_":218,"type":155},"8706",{"_":157,"mainLang":158,"languages":220},[157],{"n":74,"url":222,"height":223,"width":224,"desc":225,"surfaceType":79},"ISic001207_tiled.tif","3212px","2498px","Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas",[],[228,168,169,170,229,230,86],"Kaibel, 1890, IG","Manni Piraino, 1976, Contribution Épigraphique à l'Étude de l'esclavage en Sicile","Manganaro, 1988, La Sicilia da Sesto Pompeo a Diocleziano",[172,173,90,174,232,233,92],"R9M263EA","RZSFKACR",[235,236,237,117,121,179,97,98,99,100,180,181,182,158],"isic001207","epitaph for nemeris, a goldsmith",{"_":10},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Νεμέριε̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Γρανῶνι \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Νυμφόδωρε \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>χρυσοχόε \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>χαῖρε \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":105,"date":3,"citedRange":240,"ptr":241,"ref":243,"title":2,"citation":4},"108 fig.113",{"target":242},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/9QTE4E3Z",{"_":110,"target":110},{"file":245,"uri":245,"title":246,"status":247,"editionAuthor":11,"type":248,"objectType":249,"material":250,"condition":34,"layoutDesc":251,"handNote":255,"date":261,"places":264,"geo":267,"country":65,"region":66,"settlement":148,"repository":269,"idno":270,"textLang":272,"facsimile":274,"provenance":53,"letterHeights":279,"publications":280,"zotero":281,"keywords":282,"html":286,"bibl":287},"ISic001208","Epitaph for Oltiskos",{"_":10},{"_":117,"ana":118,"ref":119},{"_":121,"ana":122,"ref":123},{"_":179,"ana":126,"ref":127},{"layout":252},{"p":253,"rs":254,"damage":34},"Two lines of Greek letters, centred on the front face of the stone.",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},{"lettering":256,"dimensions":257},"Neat, but irregularly sized letters. Omicron is smaller than the rest and mid-line; sigma is regular with horizontal top and bottom bars; kappa is tall with short arms, slightly curving out form the middle of the upright; alpha has straight bar (and in the second case is larger; epsilon has shorter middle bar.",[258,260],{"type":39,"l":136,"from":41,"to":42,"h":259,"unit":43},"30-50",{"type":45,"l":46,"from":41,"to":42,"unit":43},{"_":262,"notBefore":263,"notAfter":210,"precision":16},"3rd — 2nd century BCE",-300,[265,266],{"_":53,"type":54,"ref":55},{"_":57,"type":58,"ref":59,"offset":60},[268],[63,64],{"_":150,"role":151,"ref":152},{"_":271,"type":155},"8702",{"_":157,"mainLang":158,"languages":273},[157],{"n":74,"url":275,"height":276,"width":277,"desc":278,"surfaceType":79},"ISic001208_tiled.tif","2021px","1540px","Scan from IGMusPal, courtesy Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas",[],[167,168,169,170,86],[172,173,90,174,92],[283,284,285,117,121,179,97,98,99,100,180,181,182,158],"isic001208","epitaph for oltiskos",{"_":10},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Ὀλτίσκος \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">